v-Electronic Engineer   
  Microsoft Asia Center for Hardware (MACH) is a fast growing and fast paced organization that is an extension of Microsoft hardware, a world leader in computer peripherals design, development and manufacturing. It is currently looking for an Electrical/System Engineer to lead its design and development activities. Versatility, tenacity, problem solving in system level, passion and an insatiable desire to learn will be essential to make your winning contribution to the continued success of MACH.
  Job Descriptions
  A successful candidate must have strong leadership skills and have the courage and conviction to make decisions in ambiguous situations. Candidate must be well prepared to manage development efforts from system level, cooperate within and across groups and functions. Ideal candidate must demonstrate strong ownership and accountability, has excellent organization and communication skills, enjoys learning, can effectively bring solutions to difficult problems, and has great attention to detail. Other key responsibilities include
  -      Propose, define and present product and platform specifications and features.
-      Ensure that designs meet established specifications, cost, timeline and development budgets.
-      Manage products development with different business models.
-      Circuit design for products as well as platforms. Including Architecture, function modules, and interface.
-      Conduct design reviews.  Be aware of short term and long term consideration. Be sure it to be within different user scenario tolerance, testable and manufacturable.
-      Ensure good documentation of the design as well as version control.
-      Manage project scope and risks.
-      Manage internal and outsourced development efforts.
-      Troubleshoot and analyze technical problems and recommend solutions.
-      Collaborate with marketing and technology teams and participate in project reviews.
  Requirements:
-      At least 6 years’ EE experience with Drawing circuit diagrams, Interpreting, analyzing and modifying logic circuit diagrams, Calculating amplitude and voltage, Basic electronics concepts
-      At least 5 years’ Field Application Engineering Experience
-      At least 5 years’ HW Turn experience
-      Familiar with Testing electronic devices
-      Good oral & written English Skills, especially EE terminology in Engli
